			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Apologies for the silence; many of us spent the weekend at Balticon 40 talking about podcasting, editing, scotch, and &#8220;Hey, I saw Neil Gaiman in the hallway!&#8221;</p>

<p>Latest news: 
Tour Asia in 2007! China is hosting an International SF/Fantasy Conference in Chengdu, August 24-27, 2007. This coincides nicely with WorldCon in Nippon, scheduled for August 30-September 3. There are even direct flights from Chengdu to Tokyo. No site link, but the full press release is at the <a href="http://www.emcit.com/wordpress/?p=2612">Emerald City Weblog</a>.</p>

<p>If you didn&#8217;t get to see Serenity as many times as you&#8217;d hoped in the theater, many cities are screening it again on Joss Whedon&#8217;s birthday (June 23 for all of you non-obsessed fans). <a href="http://www.cantstoptheserenity.com/">Learn more here.</a></p>
]]></content:encoded>
